  other people 's money and how the bankers use it , a 1914 book by louis brandeis   other people 's money , a 1916 silent film featuring gladys hulette and kathryn adams   other people 's money ( play ) , a 1987 stage drama by jerry sterner   other people 's money , a 1991 drama/comedy film based on the sterner play , starring danny devito and gregory peck   other people 's money ( novel ) , a 2011 novel by justin cartwright   a phrase attributed to milton friedman as a way of expressing the opinion that the government does not carefully spend taxpayers ' money

